HEADWORD: Friary
<hw>Fri"ar*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Friar</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Like a friar; pertaining to friars or to a
convent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Camden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Friary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Friary
<hw>Fri"ar*y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>frerie</ets>,
<ets>frairie</ets>, fr. <ets>fr⟦egrave⟧re</ets>. See
<er>Friar</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A monastery; a convent of
friars.</def> <rj><au>Drugdale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The institution or practices of friars.</def>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Friation</ent>⟦br⟧
